race.comment: IMPEL (7) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at this track over 450m behind Canya Excite Me (25.59) in a Grade 4/5. Was in the money prior to that. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. Has claims if he runs up to expectations. SIT AND STEER (1) had the drop on the lead from the rails draw last start but could only manage third, beaten 7 lengths (25.58) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 450m. Expecting another good run. LEKTRA JIMMY (3) is progressing well and looks close to another win after hitting the frame from Box 3 last run (25.50) at Warrnambool. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Overdue and gets his chance. BUSH BIG SHOW (2) justified the favourite's tag last time - another big run is on the cards.
